      Finds all claims for the list of policy numbers within the given date range.
      Parameters:

      Returns:
      QueryProcessor

    • findByPolicyNumbers

      IQueryBeanResult findByPolicyNumbers(String[] policyNumbers, Calendar beginDate, Calendar endDate, ClaimState state)
      Finds all claims for the list of policy numbers within the given date range and matching the specified claim state.
      Parameters:
      policyNumbers - The list of policy numbers to match on
      beginDate - the beginning of the loss date range
      endDate - The end of the loss date range
      state - Return claims only of the specified state (e.g. open); if null, return all claims
      Returns:
      QueryProcessor

    • findClaimByClaimNumber

      Claim findClaimByClaimNumber(String claimNumber)
      Locates and returns a single claim by claim number. If no claim with the matching claim number is found in the database, returns null.
      Parameters:
      claimNumber - the claim number to search for in the database.
      Returns:
      the found Claim object, or null if no claim found with the specified claim number.
